        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>LON­DON • Bur­ton Al­bion have reap­pointed for­mer Chelsea and Nether­lands striker Jimmy Floyd Hasselbain­k as their new man­ager to re­place Jake Bux­ton, who was dis­missed fol­low­ing Tues­day’s 4-3 home de­feat by Wigan Ath­letic, the League One (third-tier) foot­ball club said.</p>
    <p>Hasselbain­k was first named Bur­ton man­ager in Novem­ber 2014 and guided the team to the League Two (fourth-tier) ti­tle.</p>
    <p>He then left to take charge of Queens Park Rangers a year later.</p>


